"Less than 12 years ago, Conor Mcgregor was homeless. While homeless he met a woman named Dee Devlin. She took him off the streets, moved Conor into her tiny apartment and fed him daily.

All she ever asked was that he worked hard and believed in himself. She struggled to buy expensive, healthy food so Conor could train and stay focused... but she stuck by him.

ONLY 8 years ago, Conor was a plumber... barely living above poverty, but Dee stuck by him.

One saturday night, Dee sat in in attendance to once again support her man while he made over 100 MILLION dollars to add to his already successful new life.

Believe in yourself and find people to surround yourself with who believe in you as well. Life is too short to keep your circle full of people who want to watch you fail.

Don't EVER let your circumstances or people hold you down. Get out there and take what's yours! No excuses!" #Respect #StayCommitted #NeverGiveUp #GreatThingsAhead #NeverSettle #DontStop #WontStop #BigDreams #BigRewards #MakeItCount #Live #Laugh #Love #Loyal #Faith #God #Perseverance #NoDistractions #NoFear #PositiveMindset #GoodVibes #GoodPeople #FightOn #Abundance #Health #Wealth #Success #Happiness #Genius #GeniusImpact

It’s never too late to do what you love. It’s never too late to accomplish your desired dreams and goals no matter how old or young you think you are. 

Dreams may seem unattainable, but as long as you believe you can set a goal and grind daily, you can and will get closer and closer until it becomes a reality.  If you can dream it, you can achieve it. Nothing has ever been created without someone first dreaming or imagining it. Everything is possible if you believe in yourself. 

Those who constantly put you down, laugh, or tells you that you won’t achieve your goals are only reflecting their own beliefs unto you. Don’t let that stop you. Go out there and continue your journey. Never give up.
